headline: 'AI companies cannot avoid debates on regulating their tools'
description: The Trump administration opposes the regulation of artificial intelligence (AI) content, invoking freedom of expression. However, debate has intensified over the content of services like ChatGPT, particularly regarding minors, observes Le Monde's Alexandre Piquard in his column.

headline: Paris's Notre-Dame breaks attendance records nine months after reopening
description: Notre-Dame is now the most visited monument in France. Projections anticipate a total of 12 million to 13 million visitors by December 8, one year after reopening.

headline: From a Thai holiday to a Turkish prison: How two women were trapped by drug traffickers
description: The two 20-year-old women from the Paris region enjoyed an all-expenses-paid holiday in Thailand, then given suitcases packed with cannabis before their flight home. Their lawyers argued it was a case of 'great naivety.'

headline: France's 'Block Everything' protests converge around ousting Macron
description: Although France did not come to a standstill or grind to a halt on Wednesday, numerous protests took place throughout the day across the country with large gatherings in certain cities – with headcounts between 197,000 and 250,000 people – amid the firm presence of law enforcement.

headline: Behind the 'Block Everything' movement: Tight budgets and fear about the future
description: The surge in inflation in recent years is still being felt, fueling frustration among France's 'just-getting-by' population. Falling unemployment has not stopped the poverty rate from rising.
